The size of the bump being large and visible when you suck in your stomach could indicate that this emotional concern is affecting you deeply and is becoming more apparent to others, despite your attempts to hide or suppress it.

Overall, this dream suggests that you may have an unresolved emotional or personal issue that you are struggling with, and you may feel that you need assistance or support in addressing and resolving it. title: "The Elusive Ovarian Quest: A Desperate Search for Answers"

The classmate attempting to cut you with a fork and knife represents someone in your waking life who may be trying to harm or belittle you, but their efforts are ineffective because you are "raw." This may suggest that their attempts to undermine you or your self-esteem have not succeeded.

The second person trying to tear you apart with their teeth could symbolize a different individual or situation that poses a more immediate and aggressive threat to your well-being. This could represent someone who is more confrontational or directly attacking you, using more primitive and forceful methods to cause harm.

Ultimately, the dream may be highlighting your resilience and inner strength. Despite the attempts to harm you, you remain intact and undamaged. It is possible that the dream is a reflection of your subconscious processing your experiences and emotions towards situations where you feel attacked or judged.

Consider exploring any areas of your life where you may be experiencing these feelings of vulnerability or powerlessness. It may be helpful to identify the people or circumstances that are causing these emotions and find strategies to protect yourself or address the underlying issues.

Overall, this dream suggests a feeling of being pursued or threatened by an unknown force, which causes fear and uncertainty. It may be beneficial to explore any potential sources of stress or challenging relationships in your waking life. Addressing these underlying issues can help alleviate anxiety and provide a path towards resolution.

dream: I saw a barren desert; there were tumbleweeds rolling leftward. Except these tumbleweeds were red, and the weeds formed a shape of a drawn rose. But then the desert sand turned into a beach, but there were cacti in the blue horizon. And the scene was moving to the right. Then the scene changed to a soccer field. There was a boys soccer team practicing. One boy was in the goal post, and the rest of the boys were behind the goal post running around the soccer field. They were running clockwise (to the right) around the field. And then I saw a bleachers filled with many people cheering, jumping up and down with their hands raised.
interpretation:
This dream appears to be a combination of different elements and symbols, each holding its own meaning. The interpretation of dreams is subjective, but I can provide you with a possible interpretation based on the symbols presented.

The barren desert with red tumbleweeds forming a drawn rose could represent a sense of isolation or emptiness, possibly symbolizing a feeling of emotional detachment or a lack of growth in certain aspects of your life. The image of the desert transforming into a beach could indicate a shift towards a more enjoyable or refreshing phase, but the presence of cacti in the blue horizon suggests that even in positive situations, there may still be some obstacles or challenges ahead.

The scene moving to the right could represent a sense of progression or moving forward in your life. This could indicate that you are currently on a path of personal growth or development. The transition to the soccer field with the boys' team practicing may symbolize teamwork and collaboration. The boy in the goal post could represent your ability to defend or protect yourself in challenging situations. The rest of the boys running clockwise around the field could suggest a sense of order or routine in your life, as well as a desire to keep moving forward and make progress.

Finally, the image of the bleachers filled with cheering people may symbolize support, validation, or recognition from others. This could indicate that your efforts and hard work are being acknowledged and appreciated by those around you.

Overall, this dream could signify a transition from a stagnant or isolating phase to a more energized and fulfilling one. It may indicate that you are on the right path, working towards personal growth, and receiving support from others along the way. However, remember that dream interpretation is highly personal, and only you can truly decipher what these symbols mean to you within the context of your own life.
title: "Desolate Beauty: Tumbling Roses in a Shifting Sandscape, Beach Dreams and Soccer Teams"
